Class OpContext

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      java.util.HashMap<String,Object>
          ca.gedge.opgraph.OpContext
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,Object>
public final class OpContext
extends HashMap<String,Object>

A working context for OpGraphs. A context can have a parent from which it can find values.

findChildContext

public OpContext findChildContext(OpNode node)
Finds a context for the specified node. This is a deep operation which will recursively search through all child contexts to find one for the given node.

Parameters:
node - the node to get a context for
Returns:
the context for the specified node, or null if no context could be found for the given node.

the mapping of node to context

getChildContext

public OpContext getChildContext(OpNode node)
Gets a context for the specified node. If no child context currently exists for the given node, a new context will be constructed. The returned context will be parented to this context.

Parameters:
node - the node
Returns:
the context

collectValues

public <T> Map<OpNode,T> collectValues(ContextualItem field)
Collects values of a given field from all child contexts.

Parameters:
field - the field to search for
Returns:
a Map of all the values, and their associated nodes as keys (with this context having a null key)
